Available balance in KGS for all currencies at the Banks purchase rate.

The available balance is the amount of balances broken down by currencies at the purchase rate for the Banks payment cards at the time of the request. The available balance serves as a guideline. When exchange rates change, the available balance may change.
*To calculate the amount for all currencies, the purchase rate for the Banks payment cards at the time of the transaction is used.

A multiplier is a coefficient used when blocking funds when conducting a card transaction in foreign currency with the participation of multicurrency cards and it is made in soms. Also, when withdrawing funds in ATM and POS from multicurrency cards, a multiplier is applied. The final write-off of funds for transactions performed is carried out at the Banks commercial rate on the day of the transaction.
